s mummified body and then you must destroy this newly raised form and return to me its wrappings.</b><BR>Your faction standing with Truespirit got better<BR>Marl Kastane looks your way apprehensively -- he appears to be quite formidable.<BR></p><p>You get a <span class="clsItem" title="MAGIC&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;LORE&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;NO&nbsp;DROP&#x0D;WT:&nbsp;0.2&#x0D;Class:&nbsp;NONE&#x0D;Race:&nbsp;NONE"><font color=blue>Dark Shroud</font></span>.</p><p>In the ghost area of the Hole you may find a Ghost of Glohnor.</p><p>Ghost of Glohnor looks your way apprehensively -- it appears to be quite formidable.<BR>Hand the <span class="clsItem" title="MAGIC&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;LORE&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;NO&nbsp;DROP&#x0D;WT:&nbsp;0.2&#x0D;Class:&nbsp;NONE&#x0D;Race:&nbsp;NONE"><font color=blue>Dark Shroud</font></span> to a Ghost of Glohnor.</p><p><i>The ghost vanishes.</i><BR>Your faction standing with Truespirit got better</p><p>Mummy of Glohnor charges you from the basement of the ghost tower.  It does not bring any help with it.</p><p><font color=red>Mummy of Glohnor hits YOU for 270 points of damage.</font><BR>...<BR><font color=red>You have slain Mummy of Glohnor!</font><BR><font color=yellow>You gain party experience!!</font><BR></p><p class="clsMOBInfo" title="MOB Info" align="center">Deceased: Mummy of Glohnor (looks like a skeleton) - Level 56 warrior - Immune from any spells but blood line, lure line.<BR>Approximate forces required: two 50+ groups.</p><p>You get <span class="clsItem" title="MAGIC&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;LORE&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;NO&nbsp;DROP&#x0D;WT:&nbsp;0.1&#x0D;Class:&nbsp;NONE&#x0D;Race:&nbsp;NONE"><font color=blue>Head of Glohnor</font></span> and <span class="clsItem" title="MAGIC&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;LORE&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;NO&nbsp;DROP&#x0D;WT:&nbsp;0.2&#x0D;Class:&nbsp;NONE&#x0D;Race:&nbsp;NONE"><font color=blue>Glohnor wrappings</font></span> from the mummy.</p><p>Head to Paineel and hand the <span class="clsItem" title="MAGIC&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;LORE&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;NO&nbsp;DROP&#x0D;WT:&nbsp;0.1&#x0D;Class:&nbsp;NONE&#x0D;Race:&nbsp;NONE"><font color=blue>Head of Glohnor</font></span> to Gerot Kastane.</p><p><b>Gerot Kastane says 'Good travels, dark one! May Innoruuk curse your enemies!</b><BR>Your faction standing with Truespirit got better<BR>Gerot Kastane looks your way apprehensively -- he appears to be quite formidable.<BR></p><p>You get the <i><a class="clsItemLink" title="MAGIC&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;LORE&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;NO&nbsp;DROP&#x0D;STR:&nbsp;+10&nbsp;&nbsp;DEX:&nbsp;+10&nbsp;&nbsp;INT:&nbsp;+10&nbsp;&nbsp;SV&nbsp;MAGIC:&nbsp;+10&#x0D;WT:&nbsp;0.0&#x0D;Class:&nbsp;SHD&#x0D;Race:&nbsp;HUM&nbsp;ERU&nbsp;DEF&nbsp;TRL&nbsp;OGR&nbsp;IKS" target="_new" href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/item.php?id=1261">Head of the Valiant</a></i>.</p><p>Head to Kerra Isle and hand the <span class="clsItem" title="MAGIC&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;LORE&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;NO&nbsp;DROP&#x0D;WT:&nbsp;0.2&#x0D;Class:&nbsp;NONE&#x0D;Race:&nbsp;NONE"><font color=blue>Glohnor wrappings</font></span> to Marl Kastane.</p><p><b>Marl Kastane says 'You've done it! Your efforts will stand as a tribute to our kind for time eternal, my friend. Although nothing could possibly serve as a just reward for your accomplishments, please accept this as well as my eternal gratitude. It has been fashioned from the wraps of the mummy and shall protect you well.</b><BR>Your faction standing with Truespirit got better<BR>Marl Kastane looks your way apprehensively -- he appears to be quite formidable.<BR></p><p>You get the <i><a class="clsItemLink" title="MAGIC&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;LORE&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;NO&nbsp;DROP&#x0D;AC:&nbsp;40&#x0D;STR:&nbsp;+15&nbsp;&nbsp;STA:&nbsp;+10&nbsp;&nbsp;INT:&nbsp;+8&nbsp;&nbsp;HP:&nbsp;+25&#x0D;SV&nbsp;FIRE:&nbsp;+15&nbsp;&nbsp;SV&nbsp;MAGIC:&nbsp;+10&#x0D;WT:&nbsp;1.0&#x0D;Class:&nbsp;SHD&#x0D;Race:&nbsp;HUM&nbsp;ERU&nbsp;DEF&nbsp;TRL&nbsp;OGR&nbsp;IKS" target="_new" href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/item.php?id=1260">Will of Innoruuk</a></i>.</p><p>You get the <i><span class="clsItem" title="MAGIC&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;LORE&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;NO&nbsp;DROP&#x0D;WT:&nbsp;0.1&#x0D;Class:&nbsp;NONE&#x0D;Race:&nbsp;NONE"><font color=blue>Heart of the Innocent</font></span></i> by combining the <span class="clsItem" title="MAGIC&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;LORE&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;NO&nbsp;DROP&#x0D;WT:&nbsp;0.2&#x0D;Class:&nbsp;NONE&#x0D;Race:&nbsp;NONE"><font color=blue>Heart of Kyrenna</font></span> with the <span class="clsItem" title="Container&#x0D;LORE&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;NO&nbsp;DROP&#x0D;WT:&nbsp;0.5&#x0D;Capacity:&nbsp;2"><font color=blue>Soulcase</font></span>.<p><hr size="5" color=black><center><h3>The Lift of the Curse or Back to the Dead</h3></center><p>Head to City of Mist.</p><p>Lhranc looks your way apprehensively -- looks like quite a gamble.</p><p>Hand the <a class="clsItemLink" title="MAGIC&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;LORE&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;NO&nbsp;DROP&#x0D;Skill:&nbsp;1H&nbsp;Slashing&nbsp;&nbsp;Atk&nbsp;Delay:&nbsp;34&#x0D;DMG:&nbsp;16&#x0D;Effect:&nbsp;Dismiss&nbsp;Undead&#x0D;WT:&nbsp;9.5&#x0D;Class:&nbsp;SHD&#x0D;Race:&nbsp;HUM&nbsp;ERU&nbsp;DEF&nbsp;TRL&nbsp;OGR&nbsp;IKS" target="_new" href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/item.php?id=3434">Corrupted Ghoulbane</a>, the <span class="clsItem" title="MAGIC&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;LORE&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;NO&nbsp;DROP&#x0D;WT:&nbsp;0.1&#x0D;Class:&nbsp;NONE&#x0D;Race:&nbsp;NONE"><font color=blue>Heart of the Innocent</font></span>, the <a class="clsItemLink" title="MAGIC&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;LORE&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;NO&nbsp;DROP&#x0D;STR:&nbsp;+10&nbsp;&nbsp;DEX:&nbsp;+10&nbsp;&nbsp;INT:&nbsp;+10&nbsp;&nbsp;SV&nbsp;MAGIC:&nbsp;+10&#x0D;WT:&nbsp;0.0&#x0D;Class:&nbsp;SHD&#x0D;Race:&nbsp;HUM&nbsp;ERU&nbsp;DEF&nbsp;TRL&nbsp;OGR&nbsp;IKS" target="_new" href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/item.php?id=1261">Head of the Valiant</a>, and the <a class="clsItemLink" title="MAGIC&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;LORE&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;NO&nbsp;DROP&#x0D;AC:&nbsp;40&#x0D;STR:&nbsp;+15&nbsp;&nbsp;STA:&nbsp;+10&nbsp;&nbsp;INT:&nbsp;+8&nbsp;&nbsp;HP:&nbsp;+25&#x0D;SV&nbsp;FIRE:&nbsp;+15&nbsp;&nbsp;SV&nbsp;MAGIC:&nbsp;+10&#x0D;WT:&nbsp;1.0&#x0D;Class:&nbsp;SHD&#x0D;Race:&nbsp;HUM&nbsp;ERU&nbsp;DEF&nbsp;TRL&nbsp;OGR&nbsp;IKS" target="_new" href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/item.php?id=1260">Will of Innoruuk</a> to Lhranc.</p><p><b>Lhranc says 'Ahh, at last I can free myself of this prison! Centuries have passed since I enjoyed the fruits of mortality.' He hurls the components above his head where they remain suspended in midair. They hover in place while he chants the words of an ancient spell. As he speaks, the items begin to rotate around his head, slowly at first, then faster as the chanting grows louder, until it spins in a blur. Soon, the room is filled with a deafening shriek that pierces you to the core.</b><BR>Your faction standing with Truespirit got better<BR></p><p>You get <span class="clsItem" title="No info."><font color=blue>Lhranc's Coin</font></span>.</p><p><i>Lhranc appears as a human.</i><BR>Lhranc looks your way apprehensively -- what would you like your tombstone to say?<BR><BR>After a brief pause...<BR><BR><b>Lhranc says 'Young one, you cannot fathom how long it has been since I breathed air and felt flesh on my bones. I told you I would show you a weapon that would make you the most powerful of your kind. I said nothing of giving it to you. Feast your eyes on Innoruuk's Curse mortal, thank you for your service.</b><BR></p><p>If you are not satisfied with his answer, you better start using some force.</p><p><font color=red>Auto attack on.</font><BR><font color=red>Lhranc slashes YOU for 385 points of damage.</font><BR>...<BR><font color=red>You have slain Lhranc!</font><BR><font color=yellow>You gain party experience!!</font><BR></p><p class="clsMOBInfo" title="MOB Info" align="center">Deceased: Lhranc - Level 63+ shadowknight - Immune from any spells.  Procs Soul Devour (500 point direct damage) and has very fast refresh time on Harm Touch.<BR>Approximate forces required: five 50+ groups.</p><p>Marl Kastane appears near by.</p><p><b>Marl Kastane says 'Alas, I cannot be the one to carry the sword back to my people as proof in fear they will kill me to possess it for their own. I think a simple trade is in order, perhaps you have a symbol or token of Lhanrc's that I could take back to the others to ease their worries?</b><BR></p><p>Hand the <span class="clsItem" title="No info."><font color=blue>Lhranc's Coin</font> to Marl Kastane.</p><p><b>Marl Kastane says 'Very good, I will go deliver this right away.</b><BR></p><p>You recieve the <a class="clsItemLink" title="MAGIC&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;LORE&nbsp;ITEM&nbsp;&nbsp;NO&nbsp;DROP&#x0D;Skill:&nbsp;2H&nbsp;Slashing&nbsp;&nbsp;Atk&nbsp;Delay:&nbsp;45&#x0D;DMG:&nbsp;40&#x0D;STR:&nbsp;+20&nbsp;&nbsp;DEX:&nbsp;+15&nbsp;&nbsp;INT:&nbsp;+15&nbsp;&nbsp;HP:&nbsp;+60&#x0D;MANA:&nbsp;+40&nbsp;&nbsp;SV&nbsp;FIRE:&nbsp;+10&nbsp;&nbsp;SV&nbsp;DISEASE:&nbsp;+5&nbsp;&nbsp;SV&nbsp;COLD:&nbsp;+10&#x0D;SV&nbsp;MAGIC:&nbsp;+15&nbsp;&nbsp;SV&nbsp;POISON:&nbsp;+5&#x0D;Effect:&nbsp;Soul&nbsp;Consumption&#x0D;WT:&nbsp;5.0&#x0D;Class:&nbsp;SHD&#x0D;Race:&nbsp;HUM&nbsp;ERU&nbsp;DEF&nbsp;TRL&nbsp;OGR&nbsp;IKS" target="_new" href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/item.php?id=3445">Innoruuk's Curse</a>.</p><hr size="5" color=black><p></p></font></td></tr></table></font></p></font></p>
	
